1970 copyright Pat Rocco, Bizarre Productions

From the VHS box:
"Mondo Rocco" is comprised of numerous short films, providing the viewer with a well-rounded taste of the Rocco style. "Homosexuals on the March" is a document of demonstrations led by the Rev. Troy Perry of the Metropolitan Community Church; "A Night at Joanie's" features early performances by the legendary Jim Bailey; "The Room" is a classic erotic vignette, featuring the incredible sexuality of stars Ron Dilly (a James Dean look-a-like) and Mark McKane; "Screen Test" is another of Rocco's legendary voyeuristic peeks at masculinity, featuring Brian Reynolds and Jim Cassidy.
